line_1: Some rhyme to court the countra clash,
line_2: Some rhyme a neebor's name to lash;

line_1: Some rhyme to court the countra clash,
line_2: Some rhyme, (vain thought!) for needfu' cash;

line_1: Some rhyme to court the countra clash,
line_2: For me, an aim I never fash;

line_1: Will with your virtue, peace, or interest, clash;
line_2: The peevish, sullen, shrewd, luxurious, rash,

line_1: The casements they clatter; chains rattle; doors clash,
line_2: Loud bellows the thunder; blue lightnings still flash;

line_1: Hence all that interferes, and dares to clash
line_2: With indolence and luxury, is trash;
